steps.description:
Remove unnecessary .clone() in export() (review bug #1 — unnecessary_allocation). Change lines 179-185 from:
  let compiled = self.compiled.as_ref().ok_or_else(|| ...)?.clone();
  let result = self.engine.build(&compiled, format);
to:
  let compiled = self.compiled.as_ref().ok_or_else(|| ...)?;
  let result = self.engine.build(compiled, format);
This works because self.compiled (immutable borrow) and self.engine (mutable borrow for build) are disjoint fields — Rust's borrow checker allows simultaneous disjoint field borrows. Eliminates full CompiledModule clone (templates, value cells, constraints, diagnostics) on every export call.
